args:
Lathna and Cleo form a bond of mutual trust.
The pair's feelings win out against Nyarlathotep,
and the incident is safely resolved at last. That
night, the two return to the festival venue and
join hands like sisters to enjoy the festivities.
Just a little farther! Once we pass through\nthis street, we'llâ€”oh!

Foolish, frail insects who would leap into
flame of their own volition. Are you truly
in such a hurry to cut free the threads of
your life?
There you are, foul one. We won't permit\nyou to continue doing as you please!\nHaaah!
Fleeting resistance. An aimless, worthless\nattempt. However much you insects warble\nyour defiance, I will weather your storm.
I'm...okay! But he just repelled my attack.\nWe're no match for him as things stand!
Give yourselves as sacrifice unto the\nAncient One. Yield to the sweet embrace\nof the End, and perish.
(Ngh... He's about to attack again!\nIf I don't find some way to protect her,\nLathna's going toâ€”)

We are Chaos. The servant who sets
the Ancient One's salver with offerings
of flesh. From beyond the darkness,
feel Our breath...
ï¼‚No... This... This isn't what I want...\nAAAAH!ï¼‚
A miscalculation. A fragment of the frail\nsoul still lives within Us. A terrible error.
Did the woman's soul stop him from\nwithin...?
Probably. He must not have complete\ncontrol of her body yet. We might still\nbe able to do this!
If you regret your profane deeds,\nthen please, stop all this!

To trample over the dignity of the dead,
and to be reduced to a monster of
blasphemy... If that is not what you
desire, then please, answer me!
Nyarlathotep is in pain. Your voice is\ngiving the woman the courage to fight,\nCleo. I'm sure of it.
If you would offer courage, so would I.
My love... It's me! I'm here! I'll fight him\ntogether with you! Please, let me help you!

Foolish dreams are just that. To cling to
a stagnant flicker is gutless esurience.
You insects will be as ash dusting a tomb,
ushered to silent oblivion.
Watch out! He's going to put\neverything on the line with one attack!
No... The entire town and its people are\nin danger!
Worry not. I'll manage something, I swear!

Now that the woman is holding him back,
I should be able to overcome his attack by
hitting him with the strongest magic I can
wield.
I'm going to start chanting it. But I'll be\ndefenseless in the meantime, so...
Will you believe in me and support me,\nLathna? I ask this as your dear friend.
Yeah... Okay. I'm right behind you, Cleo.\nBecause that's exactly where I want to be.
Thank you. Here I go.\nO ancient spirits, servants of the wood!
Chaos, the Unknown, the End, Rebirth...\nWith Our power, We shall eliminate all\nthat opposes Us. Eliminate. Eliminate.
Wind stirring the boughs, the bustle of the\nwood, the joy of its sweet tune... Ugh!
It's okay. I'm here. It's my turn to\nsupport you as much as you did me!

I hear the voice of the earth that echoes,
and I pray. I pray to destroy the evil here
in the name of purity. I dedicate all my
prayers to this, here and now.
O spirits, be my strength!\nAncient Star Ray!
E L I M I N A T E!
Eek! I can't see what happened!\nDid Nyarlathotep...? Aaaaah!

We are Chaos. Our Quietus is our Genesis.
We are but one Nyarlathotep of many.
We have yet countless Emissaries,
uncountable in name and form...

The hope that our brethren held is but a
false dream, transient. It is fated to one
day be lost and fade. The Dusk ends.
O Ancient One, forgive Our ignorance.
It seems he escaped. Nonetheless, we've\nstopped anyone else from getting hurt.
Oh... The zombies are all disappearing,\ntoo.
Nyarlathotep is gone, and so all who\nwere trapped within him are free.
Yes. The souls of the people I desecrated\nshould finally be able to return to mana.
Ma'am! So you were freed as well.
Yes. At last, my wife has returned to me.\nAll of it is thanks to you two.
I am deeply grateful to you for stopping\nthe barbarity I unleashed.
I went mad with my sorrow and did\nsomething unforgivable...and alone,\nI could not resist Nyarlathotep.
Truly, thank you. You brave and\nkind-hearted young women.
ï¼‚Thank youï¼‚... I thought I'd never hear\nthose words again.

I thought that I was burdened with
something frightful, and I convinced
myself that no matter how hard I tried,
I could never do good.
But I was wrong. Maybe it's okay for\nme to believe that I can help people.
Of course it is. No matter who you are,\nif you want to do right by others, that\nresolve is all you need.
Do you see? So long as you're yourself,\neven if you ARE Nyarlathotep, there is\nnothing to worry about.
Who you MIGHT be isn't important.\nHeck, no one really knows who they\nactually are, anyway!
So instead of trying so hard to figure out\nwho you are, you ought to think about\nwho you WANT to be.
(That's right. I lost my way for a bit,\nbut I've finally remembered something\nimportant.)
...It's time. We must go, but know\nthat we are forever in your debt.
Farewell, spirits. I'll... I'll do my best.
Wooow, so pretty!\nThey're even brighter than before...

With the zombie crisis at an end, the
festival has resumed. I've been told
they're re-sending the lanterns
that flowed upriver.
Because of that, there are more lanterns\npassing by than usual. Come, let's hurry\nand get our own in the water.
Okay, so we light the candle, put it inside\nthe lantern, and then set it on the river...
And then we pray. Like this...

The ghosts...and my parents. I've probably
had them worried ever since I lost them,
so I wanted them to know that I'm finally
okay.
It wasn't easy to get here, but now\nI can say I've got a kind big sister.
Oh, Lathna...! Yes. You certainly do.
(I feel so happy. Perhaps even a little\nbit awkward.)
(Myriam... Is this how you felt back then,\ntoo?)

Being a big sister comes with certain
responsibilities. Good thing I'm up for
the challenge! I'll make certain you
enjoy the festival this time, all right?
What would you like to do? The ring toss,\nor the goldfish scoop? Or perhaps a\nculinary tour of all the food stalls?
They're sure to have all the staples:\nyakisoba, shaved ice, and the like. Tell me\nwhat sounds best, and I'll get it for you.
Anything is good, so long as you're with\nme, Cleo. I'm happy to try whatever you\nthink is tastiest.
And...it would make me happy if\nwe could hold hands while we do.\n...Unless that's not okay?
Of course it's okay. Now, take your big\nsister's hand. We have a festival to enjoy.
The night is young, and so are we.\nThis is only the beginning for us.
Yeah. If I could have a wish granted...\nIt would be to stay together with all the\npeople who are important to me...
Forever, so long as I am myself.
